<div class="jumbotron">

  <h1>Barcoding the German Flora - GBoL5</h1>
  <h2>A project of the German Barcode of Life Initiative <a href="http://www.bolgermany.de">(GBoL)</a></h2>
  <h3>Funded by the Federal Ministry of Education and Research</h3>

  <p>GBoL5 aims to provide a curated reference collection for the approximately 4,800 native land plant species (bryophytes, lycophytes, ferns and seed plants) of the German flora with a linkage to specific sequence data (DNA barcodes). To ensure identification success GBoL5 generates sequence data for up to four fast evolving molecular markers from two genomes<!--(klick here for more information)-->.

    GBoL5 is a joint initiative of the <a href="http://www.nees.uni-bonn.de">Nees Institute for Plant Biodiversity (NEES, University of Bonn)</a>, the <a href="http://ieb.uni-muenster.de"> Institute for Evolution and Biodiversity (IEB, University of Münster)</a>, the <a href="http://www.bgbm.org/"> Botanical Garden and Botanical Museum Berlin (BGBM, Freie Universität Berlin)</a> and the Stuttgart State Museum of Natural History (SMNS).</p>

